Here is the implementation in Python using the `burnysc2` package:

```python
from sc2.bot_ai import BotAI
from sc2.ids.unit_typeid import UnitTypeId
from sc2.position import Point2

class MicroBot(BotAI):
    async def on_step(self, iteration: int):
        # Get our units
        colossus = self.units(UnitTypeId.COLOSSUS).first
        stalkers = self.units(UnitTypeId.STALKER)
        zealots = self.units(UnitTypeId.ZEALOT)

        # Get enemy units
        enemy_colossus = self.enemy_units.of_type(UnitTypeId.COLOSSUS).first
        enemy_stalkers = self.enemy_units.of_type(UnitTypeId.STALKER)
        enemy_zealots = self.enemy_units.of_type(UnitTypeId.ZEALOT)

        # Colossus strategy: Engage the enemy Colossus
        if colossus and enemy_colossus:
            colossus.attack(enemy_colossus)

        # Stalkers strategy: Focus on enemy Zealots and Stalkers
        if stalkers:
            for stalker in stalkers:
                if enemy_zealots:
                    closest_enemy_zealot = enemy_zealots.closest_to(stalker)
                    stalker.attack(closest_enemy_zealot)
                elif enemy_stalkers:
                    closest_enemy_stalker = enemy_stalkers.closest_to(stalker)
                    stalker.attack(closest_enemy_stalker)

        # Zealots strategy: Engage in melee combat with enemy Zealots
        if zealots:
            for zealot in zealots:
                if enemy_zealots:
                    closest_enemy_zealot = enemy_zealots.closest_to(zealot)
                    zealot.attack(closest_enemy_zealot)
                elif enemy_stalkers:
                    closest_enemy_stalker = enemy_stalkers.closest_to(zealot)
                    zealot.attack(closest_enemy_stalker)
```

This code defines a basic micro-management strategy for your units. The Colossus will engage the enemy Colossus, while the Stalkers and Zealots will focus on the enemy Zealots and Stalkers. The Zealots will engage in melee combat, and the Stalkers will use their ranged attacks.
